T1  - Risk-Neutral Parameter Shifts and Derivatives Pricing in Discrete Time
AU  - SCHRODER, MARK
Y1  - 2004/10/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/10/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.2004.00702.x
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 2375
EP  - 2402
VL  - 59
IS  - 5
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.2004.00702.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT We obtain a large class of discrete-time risk-neutral valuation relationships, or ?preference-free? derivatives pricing models, by imposing a simple restriction on the state-price density process. The risk-neutral stock-return and forward-rate dynamics are obtained by changing only a location parameter, which can be determined independent of the preference and true location parameters. The Gaussian models of Rubinstein (1976), Brennan (1979), and Câmera (2003), and the gamma model of Heston (1993) are all special cases. The model provides simple relationships between expected returns and state-price density parameters analogous to the diffusion case.
ER  - 

